AGI - Canton police in Ohio posted a video of a police officer's camera on the night that a 53-year-old African died after repeatedly telling agents "I can't breathe" while he was handcuffed with his hands behind his back and nailed to the ground. The Nbc site writes it, referring to a story that reminds many of George Floyd's death in Minneapolis on May 25, 2020. In the 18 April video, the man, Frank Tyson, is on the floor of a bar for more than 5 minutes before the police controls his wrist and about 8 minutes before the resuscitation is started. In the video, almost 36 minutes long, you can see the police that intervenes on the scene of a car accident where you find a light pole knocked down and a vehicle not busy with the driver's door open and an airbag activated. A man in a white van whose face is blurred, passes and tells the police that the responsible man is in a lodge down the street. Agents come in and a woman asks them to take Tyson away. When the agents approach him, he drops a bar stool and tells them to call the sheriff. Then they try to cuff him.&nbsp;
